Commentary: Bounce and swing in the first ball! Ishant starts with a good length ball outside off. Crawley leaves it alone. The ball steeps on its way to Rishabh Pant. He fumbles but does well. It is going to be a tough test for the keepers.
Full and outside off. The ball jags back in but Crawley is aware of his off pole and leaves it alone. It wobbles as it goes to Pant and this is going to be a challenge for him behind the stumps.
Good length ball around off, Crawley taps it to point.
Not a lot of swing on this one as this is easily left alone by Crawley.
This one keeps low and dies on its way to Pant! Full outside off, Crawley shoulders arms to it. The ball dies on its way to Pant.
Another one that keeps low. Good length ball on off, Crawley does well to adapt to the bounce and block it. Maiden over to begin with. Good start for Ishant on his 100th Test!
Bumrah gets some away movement first up. He starts with a good length ball wide outside off. It shapes away from Sibley and he is happy to let it carry to the keeper.
Length ball wide outside off and shaping away from the right-hander. Sibley shoulders arms to it. Two away swingers, will now be the time for the inswinger?
Yes it is! Late inswing this time. Good length ball outside off, Sibley leaves it. The ball comes back in but after it goes past the stumps.
Good amount of away swing on this one. Good length ball pitching outside off and swinging away. It swings a lot. Pant does well to dive and save it.
Bumrah is coming closer to the stumps now. Good length ball pitching around off, it swings away and Sibley is yet to get bat on ball.
Sibley gets bat on ball! Good length ball on off, this is the inswinger. Sibley defends it with a straight bat to see off the over. Good start for Bumrah too!
Length ball around off, Crawley hangs on the back foot as he dead bats it onto the pitch.
A fuller one from Ishant and Crawley cannot get it past the fielder as he hits it to mid on. Still no runs on the board for England.

A shout for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Ishant slides one onto the middle and leg, Crawley looks to whip it across square leg but misses it. The ball takes the pads and goes to the square leg region. A leg bye taken. Hang on it is also a No Ball. Ishant has overstepped.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a start from Ishant and India! Brilliant piece of bowling from him. He kept it outside off the entire previous over and this time gets the ball to land in the channel around off, Sibley hangs on the back foot as he looks to defend it. The ball though shapes away a bit to catch the outside edge of Dom's bat. It flies to the second slip where Rohit takes the catch.
Length and around off, Bairstow makes a watchful leave. And Ishant oversteps once again. No ball called.
Back of a length and outside off, Bairstow blocks it to the off side from within the crease.
Coming in with the angle after pitching on a length and Bairstow safely negotiates it with a push down the ground off the back foot.
Good length and in the channel around off, Bairstow does not offer a stroke to it. Still no runs off the bat.

FOUR! First runs off the bat! Good looking shot! Crawley gets off the mark here. Just timing on this one. Full and angled on middle, Zak drives it through the gap between mid on and mid-wicket as the ball races to the fence for the first boundary.
Now, Bumrah bowls a length ball but the line is too wide outside off, the ball further moves away from Crawley who does not show interest to play at it.
Good length and around off, Zak taps it towards mid-wicket and hares for a quick single.

Beautifully done! Lovely piece of bowling! Right line and length from Bumrah. Length ball a nip backer from Jasprit as Bairstow looks to defend it off the back foot. The ball just swing away past his outside edge and dips onto Pant who gets fingertips as the ball drops onto the turf.
On a length and around off, Jonny taps it to the leg side this time.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Jonny.
Full and on off, Crawley dead bats it from within the crease on the surface this time.
Length ball swinging away from Zak, Crawley just watches the ball and then decides to leave it.
Another watchful leave from Crawley. This one though does not swing much after landing on a length but instead goes straight to Pant.

FOUR! Glorious looking drive! Ishant errs in length and line as he overpitches it around off, Crawley leans and then strokes it all along the carpet past the outstretched hands of Ishant and into the fence at long off for a boundary.

FOUR! And another! Lovely timing! The ball is leaving his bat sumptuously! Full and angled on middle, Crawley clips it through the gap between mid on and mid-wicket as the ball runs away to the fence for another boundary.
Short of good length around leg, Crawley tucks it off his hips and towards square leg for a couple of runs.

Length and angled down leg, Bairstow looks to turn it to the leg side but he misses it as the ball takes the thigh pad and rolls to the square leg region. A leg bye taken. A half-hearted appeal too but nothing doing from the umpire.
Just short of the fielder there! Length and around off, Crawley takes the defensive mode but outside edges it towards point where it falls short of Rahane.
FOUR! Gorgeous hit! Crawley is looking in full flow. Bumrah dishes a fuller one and Crawley takes a full toll off it as he drives it through covers for a boundary.
Good length and around off, Crawley is well aware of his off pole as he makes a leave.
And another one in the channel outside off, Crawley leaves it alone.
FOUR! Crawley makes it look so easy! Full and on the pads, Crawley flicks it through square leg as the ball races to the fence. Poor stuff from Bumrah there.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! Not the best of the returns for Bairstow! He departs for a duck. Arm ball from Axar Patel as Bairstow fails to pick him up. He plays for the defensive push but does not cover the line. He misses but he ball does not as it raps him onto his pads. There is an appeal and the finger goes up. Bairstow straightaway reviews it. The replays roll in as the Ultra Edge comes on and shows that there is no bat involved. Now, time for Ball Tracker as it shows Three Reds, Bairstow departs and takes one of the reviews too along with him.
Little bit of confusion but safe in the end. Floated on leg, Root turns it behind square on the leg side. They look for a run but then opt against it.
Ohh! Didn't carry! Quicker and shorter on middle and off, Root looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pad. The ball falls just short of the man at short leg.
Good leave! Risky but good. Flatter trajectory delivery outside off, Root leaves it. The ball turns in and misses the off pole by just a little.
Floated on off, Root pushes it to cover. He wants the run but once again a little confusion and Crawley sends him back.

Root is off the mark! Shorter on off and middle, Root whips it through mid-wicket and gets a couple. End of a superb first over from Axar Patel. A wicket to begin with and a brace to end. A lot of questions asked between those two events.
Length ball around off, Crawley taps it to point.
BEATEN! Nearly another wicket! Full and around off, swinging away from Zak. Crawley leans and goes for an expansive drive but is beaten all ends up.
Length and around off, Crawley nudges it to the leg side now.
Good length and on off, Zak blocks it to the off side.
Length ball angled on middle, Crawley looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets in a tangle there as the ball drops in front of his boots.
Good length ball outside off, played to gully this time.
Tossed up on off, Root defends it out.
Floated on middle, Root blocks it off the inner half of the bat as the ball rolls to square leg. A single taken.
On middle, kept out by Crawley.
Flatter on off, Zak is forward in defense.
And again Zak is happy to dead bat this tossed up ball from Patel.
Crawley blocks this flighted ball around off to see off the over.
Length ball around off, Root stands tall as he defends it out to the off side.
Fuller and angled on off, Root has no issue in tapping this one back down the ground to mid on.

Uneven bounce! Good length and around off, the ball rares from there as Root lines up to defend. The ball hits his fingers. He does well in the end to take his one hand off the bat as he defends it in the end. He looks to be in some pain there as the physio rushes out to the middle.
Short of good length around off, Root gets on top of the bounce as he plays it to gully.
Length and outside off, late away swing this time for Bumrah as Root leaves it for the keeper to do the rest.
Fuller and around off, Root tries to play it late as he waits for the ball to defend it to point. A maiden over from Bumrah.
Flatter and around middle, Zak blocks it off the back foot.
Spin for Axar! That is venomous! Arm ball pitched on off, the ball grips the surface and the ball turns away past the outside edge of Crawley's defensive push.
FOUR! Simple gorgeous! Full and around off, Zak leans into the drive as he caresses it through covers for a boundary.
On middle, kept out off the front foot.
Floated on off, Zak defends it out safely.
Looped up ball around off, Crawley is happy to block it out.
Length and outside off, from Ishant in his new spell. Root has no business to play at it.
Another length ball outside off, no movement on this one as Root has an easy leave to make.
Good length but the line is well outside off, Root won't even look at them as he makes yet another leave.
Fuller one on off, Root strokes it back to the bowler. Ishant tries to field in his followthrough but the boot gets stuck in the surface as he tumbles on the ground.
Nothing doing for Root on this length ball outside off. Just leave it alone.
FOUR! That is Roooooot! Full and around off, Root hangs on the back foot and drives it straight down the ground to long off for a boundary. That should do a lot of good for the English skipper.
Darted on leg, tucked to mid on for a quick single.

Big turn there! Tossed up outside off, spinning away from Root, Joe goes for the drive but is beaten as the ball bounces a bit extra to beat the outside edge. The keeper too fails to collect as the first slip takes it.
On middle, turned to the leg side for a single.
Tossed up on middle and turning down leg, Zak misses his defensive push to get hit on the pads. Half an appeal from the bowler but nothing doing.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and wide outside off, Crawley cuts but cannot get it past covers. A single though taken.
FOUR! Crawley is going great guns at the moment! Full and around middle, Zak Crawley flicks it through mid-wicket as the ball beats the man there in the deep for a boundary.
On middle, Zak pushes it to mid on. Root looks for a single but is sent back.

FOUR! England would be happy with Crawley back in the squad. He has just looked unfluttered with anything. Full and around off, Zak leans into it and creams it to long off for another boundary in that region.
Length and outside off, Crawley does not fiddle with it.
Fuller and outside off, Zak controls his instincts as he leaves it alone.
Full and on the pads, Crawley clips it to deep mid-wicket. Axar Patel in the deep does the mopping up act. A couple taken. 50-up for England.
Slower and on middle, Root turns it to mid-wicket for a single.
Darted on middle, Crawley dead bats it.
On middle, blocked out off the back foot by Crawley.
Beaten! Tossed up ball around off, Crawley is drawn on the front foot as he looks to defend. The ball turns away at the last instance from him to beat the outside edge.
On off, Zak gets right behind the ball as he defends it out.
On middle, turned to square leg for a single.
Ashwin starts with a floated delivery on middle, Crawley milks it to long on for a single.
Darted fuller on leg, Root defends it away from short leg.
Floated on off, Root defends it.
Shorter on middle, Root dabs it in front of short leg.
Around the pads, Root flicks it to the leg side and gets to the other end.
Dot to finish the over. Unlike Axar no success in the first over for Ravichandran Ashwin. The last ball is a tossed up ball on the stumps, Crawley defends it with a straight bat.
On the pads, Root flicks it to backward square leg.
Another shortish ball on the pads. Root dabs it to the left of backward square leg and gets a single.
Absolute beauty from Axar! Gives this one air and makes it drift away from Crawley from around off. Crawley keeps his bat at off pole and it goes past it.
This one turns back in. It is on off and middle, Crawley pushes it to mid on.
Good running! Floated on off, Crawley pushes it to the right of mid off and takes a quick run. Washington Sundar has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Floated on the stumps, Root keeps it out.
Shorter on leg, Crawley defends it on the leg side.
Tossed up on middle, Crawley defends it with a straight bat.
Flighted on off, Crawley keeps it out.
Turn and bounce on this one. It is on middle, Crawley defends it off the higher part of his bat.
On the stumps, Crawley calmly defends it.
Tossed up on middle, Zak Crawley sweeps it to the leg side and keeps the strike.
FOUR! That is a glorious shot! You can watch this in loop and you'll still want more. Half volley on off, Crawley gets on his front foot and drives it through covers for a boundary.

Superb delivery! Bowls a round arm action delivery. It pitches on off, Crawley gets on his front foot to defend. The ball turns and bounces as it beats the outside edge off Zak's willow and goes past the off pole.

FOUR! SLAMMED! FIFTY FOR CRAWLEY! This has been a wonderful knock and a perfect comeback into the side for him. It has not been easy to bat on but he has been at it from ball one. Short and spinning away, Crawley stays on his back foot and punches it through covers to get a boundary and get his fifty. He has impressed one and all in this innings but now he will need to kick on and convert this into a hundred.
On off and short, Crawley knocks it to the off side and gets to the other end.

Appeal for LBW but a hopeful one and nothing else. Floated outside off, Root lunges forward and looks to sweep but gets hit on the pad. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Pitched outside off.
Flighted on off, Root keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Crawley goes for the reverse sweep but cannot get it past the man at backward point.
On off, Crawley defends it out.

NOT OUT! UMPIRE'S CALL! Crawley is saved by a whisker! Tossed up around off, Crawley looks to defend it but is beaten as the ball spins away from him to hit him on the thigh pad. There is an appeal but the umpire does not give it in. Kohli takes the review as the Ultra Edge comes on and there is no bat involved. Now comes the Ball Tracker which shows umpire's call on hitting the wickets. Zak is saved in the end.
On middle, Zak keeps it out.
Another floated ball on middle, Zak is solid in defense.
On off, kept out safely.
FOUR! Easy doing! Full and on middle, Root glances it fine down to fine leg as the ball races to the fence for a boundary.
Flatter on middle, clipped to mid-wicket for a single by Root.
On off, Crawley blocks it off the front foot.
Slider around off, Zak looks to play it off the back foot but he gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Floated on off, Crawley fails to read the ball as it spins past his outside edge this time.
On off, pushed to covers.
Full and on middle, driven down to long on for a single.
Full around off, Zak goes for the reverse sweep but plays it to cover-point for a single.
On leg, clipped to mid-wicket.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler this time by Root.

OUT! Crawley survives due to Umpire's call but Root is not that lucky as he falls prey to it. England in all sorts of trouble as they lose their skipper. India ruling the roost at the moment with both Axar and Ashwin asking question on every ball. Tosed up around middle, it is the straighter one from Ashwin as Root looks to defend it. He plays for the turn but there isn't any as he misses it to get hit flush on the knee roll. Root does not think he is out as he takes the review. The replays roll in and there is no bat involved confirms the Ultra Edge. Ball Tracker shows Umpire's Call on hitting the stumps. A big, big wicket and it can be seen from the Indian skipper's celebration.

Edgy way to start! Floated on middle and leg, Stokes looks to defend but gets an inside edge. No short leg in place so he survives. The ball goes behind square leg and Stokes gets off the mark with a single.
Floated on middle, Stokes defends it off his back foot.
Flighted outside off, Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the back pad. Muted appeal but nothing serious.
Shorter on middle and off, Stokes whips it to short mid-wicket.
On the pads, Stokes defends it to the leg side.
Tossed up outside off, Stokes lunges forward and defends it onto the ground.
Flighted around off, Stokes sweeps it to the left of deep square leg for a single. He keeps the strike. 23 overs done. England are 76/3!
Floated on leg, Stokes comes down the track and looks to defend but the ball hits him on his pad.
On the pads, Stokes flicks it but cannot go past mid-wicket.
Flighted around off, Stokes lunges forward and defends it.
FOUR! Up and over! Stokes puts on his dancing shoes and gets his first boundary of the game. Floated on middle and off, Stokes comes down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Stokes goes back to defending and blocks this onto the ground.
Tossed up on off and middle, Stokes defends it.
Flatish delivery on middle, Crawley defends it off his back foot.
Tossed up outside off and it keeps straight after pitching. Crawley leaves it alone and luckily for him it misses the off pole.
Turn on this one! Floated on off, Crawley looks to defend but the ball turns and goes past the outside edge.

OUT! LBW! The man who was looking well-set and has scored the bulk of the runs in this innings is out of here and India get their 4th wicket of the session. Axar gets his second of the game and India are all over England like a rash! Floated delivery pitching on middle, this one keeps straight and on a pitch where the ball is turning, the one that does not turn is more dangerous. Crawley gets on his front foot and looks to defend. He plays for the spin but there is none on this delivery. The ball hits him on the pad. A huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Crawley has a chat with Stokes and they decide not to review it.
Floated on off, Axar is making the ball dance to his tunes. He is turning them and then the next he is making them go straight. This one turns and beats the outside edge of Pope's bat.
Floated on off, Pope defends it with a straight bat. Another solid over from Axar. It is a wicket maiden.
Tossed up around off, Stokes defends it onto the ground.
Flighted on off, Stokes blocks it.
Around the pads, Ben blocks it.
Drift, bounce and beaten! Shorter around off, Stokes gets on his back foot and looks to defend but the ball does not turn and beats the outside edge of Stokes' willow.
Flighted on off, Stokes manages to keep it out.
Darted on the pads, Stokes manages to block it on the leg side.
This one keeps low. Floated on middle, Pope manages to defend it.
On the pads, Pope flicks it to the leg side.
Floated on off, Pope comes down the track and defends it.
Once again Ollie comes down the track to negate the spin and defends it to the off side.
Darted on middle, Pope defends it to the leg side.
Pope gets off the mark in the final ball of the session. Floated on middle, Pope flicks it to deep square leg and takes a single. That will be TEA on Day 1!
Tossed up on off, Pope blocks it out off the back foot.
Floated on off, Pope comes to the pitch of the ball to keep it out.

An appeal, a huge one from Ashwin but nothing from the umpire. Tossed up around off, Pope takes a big stride forward as he looks to defend it but gets rapped on the pads. Ashwin appeals but the umpire is unmoved.

OUT! BOWLED! Ashwin strikes in the very first over of the session! Brilliant bowling as Ashwin once again spins his web around the Englishmen. Nicely tossed up ball around off, Pope prods forward to defend. He plays the original line but the ball turns away from his outside to hit the top of off pole. Half the England side is back into the hut.
On off, Foakes pushes it to the off side now.
Floated on leg, Ben presses forward to defend it to the leg side.
Floated on middle, turned towards the leg side by Stokes off the back foot.
Flighted on off, Stokes plays it back to the bowler.
Now pushes the ball back to the bowler off the front foot.
On off, Ben keeps it out from within the crease.

OUT! LBW! And once again it is the Umpire's call which has become a nemesis for the English batsmen. Tossed up around off, sliding in with the angle, Ben Stokes looks to play it off the back foot but is beaten there to get rapped on the pads. Stokes reviews it immediately and the replays roll in. No bat there confirms the Ultra Edge as the Ball Tracker shows Umpire's Call on hitting the stumps. England's vice-captain departs.
On off, kept out off the back foot by Archer.
Short around off, Foakes gets on his back foot and blocks it.
Flighted on off, Foakes defends it to the on side.
Good quick running. Tossed up on middle and off, Foakes plays it away from mid on and gets a quick single.
On the pads, Archer gets his bat down and defends it to the leg side.
FOUR! Archer is off the mark with a boundary! Floated on middle and off, Archer sweeps it through mid-wicket and gets a boundary.
Flighted slower through the air around off. Archer looks to defend but gets beaten.
Floated on middle, defended off the inner half of the bat to the leg side.
Full on off, pushed to covers.
Flighted on off, Ben defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Floated on off, Foakes defends it as the ball goes a bit uppish towards covers. Though it fell short there.
Another arm ball going with the angle. Foakes plays for the turn to get beaten. He gets rapped on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved and the Indians don't take the review.
On off, kept out.
Floated on off, pushed off the back foot.
Fuller on middle, Archer turns it to the leg side.
And again Archer turns this loopy ball to the leg side.
On middle and leg, turned behind square on the leg side for a single.
Floated on off, Foakes plays for the turn but the ball straightens to beat the outside edge of Ben's bat.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Darted on leg, turned to mid-wicket.
Loopy on off, pushed to the off side with soft hands by Archer.
Quicker and around middle, turned to short leg.
Slower through the air around off, Archer defends it to point for a single.
On off, blocked back to the bowler.
Fuller on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller on off, driven back to the bowler.
Tossed up ball on off, Archer keeps it out.
FOUR! Archer plays it powerfully! Short and wide outside off, Archer slaps it through point as the ball races to the fence there.
Flighted on middle, Archer goes for the sweep but hits it to short leg. The ball deflects towards square leg. A single taken.
Full on off, Foakes dead bats it.
On middle, turned to mid on by Foakes this time.
Darted on off, pushed off the back foot to point.

OUT! Knocked him over! Axar's straight ones are a hit here. Quicker and outside off, coming in with the angle. Don't know what Archer was thinking there as he was late to bring his bat down. The ball sneaks past his inside edge and pegs the off pole back. Just a formality remains.
On off, kept out.
Floated on off, Leach plays it from the crease there.
Full on off, Leach defends it off the front foot. The ball rolls off the outside edge towards point for a single.

Floated on off, Foakes plays it back to the bowler. Another Axar over yields a wicket and England just three wickets away from folding up in their first innings. Still they haven't reached 100 runs on the board.
DROPPED! Not really! Tossed up around off, Leach blocks it off the front foot. The ball flies off the outside edge but it falls short of the first slip fielder.
Full on off, pushed to point.
Floated on off, Leach plays it to silly point.
On off, kept out.
Flighted around off, Jack plays it safely.
On off, Leach is happy to play it out.
Floated on off, Foakes defends it with a straight bat.
Shorter on off and middle, Foakes defends it off his back foot.
Flighted on off, Foakes lunges forward and looks to defend it with soft hands. The ball hits the inside edge and goes away from short leg. Single taken.
Floated on middle and leg, Leach defends it.
Tossed up around off, Leach looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes away from the slip fielder. Two taken.
Shorter and just outside off, Leach looks to defend but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of Leach's willow.
Loopy ball on middle, Foakes flicks it behind square on the leg side and gets a single.
Floated on off and turns away a tad. Leach looks to defend but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin gets his third and Leach joins his other teammates back in the pavilion. Flighted delivery on off, Leach lunges forward to defend but the ball turns and takes the outside edge of Jack's blade. It falls to Pujara at gully. He is a very good fielder at that region. He shows good reflex and takes a very good catch inches above the ground. The umpires go upstairs just to check if the catch is a clean one. The Soft Signal is out and replays find Pujara's catch to be clean as a whistle. Leach walks back and England just 8 down with the score yet to reach the triple figure mark.
Flighted on off, Broad keeps it out.
Flighted delivery outside off. Broad drives it through covers and gets a couple to get off the mark and bring up the 100 for England.
Flighted on off, Broad keeps it out.
Shorter on middle, Foakes defends it uppishly but wide of short leg.
Tossed up on off, Foakes keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
On the stumps, BF keeps it away.
Floated on off, Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off and middle. Foakes looks to block but the ball takes the inner half of his bat and goes to the leg side. Away from Gill at short leg.
Beauty! Ashwin bowls it slower and gives this one nice air. Broad looks to defend but the ball spins and bounces away from him. Pant takes a good take behind the stumps.
Flighted on off, Broad lunges forward and defends it.
Tossed up on off, Broad looks to defend and the ball hits both bat and pad. Hits his bat first and that was the question Kohli was asking.
Flighted on off, Broad keeps it out.
Loopy and around off, pushed to cover.
Looped up around off, Broad sweeps it through square leg and keeps the strike.
Tossed up around off, Broad hangs on the back foot to block but the ball goes past the edge. Pant fails to collect it. The ball goes to the leg side towards fine leg. A leg bye taken.
Darted on off, pushed off the back foot by Foakes.
On off, Foakes lunges forward to defend it.
Fuller on off, driven down to long off for a single.
Full and around off, Broad goes for the sweep but misses it completely. The ball was not far from the off pole.
Flighted around off, Broad defends it out to the off side. The outside edge is found though but it drops short of Kohli at second slip.
Off spinner around off, Foakes keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Foakes comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on leg and middle, Broad keeps it out.

NOT OUT! Broad survives. The ball is missing the off pole and this is the first decision in this game that has been overturned. Excellent review from Broad. Flighted delivery pitching on off, Broad looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire is quick to raise his finger. Broad reviews it straightaway. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge first shows no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes on and shows that the ball spun too much and is missing the off pole.

NOT OUT! India lose one of their three reviews. Floated delivery on off, this is the carrom ball and it turns in to the southpaw. Broad lunges forward and looks to defend. He misses and gets hit on the pad. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli in the eleventh hour decides to take the review. Replay rolls in and Ball Tracker shows that the ball is missing the leg pole by another couple of stumps.
On off, pushed from within the crease by Foakes.
Flighted around off, pushed to point.
On middle, turned past the short leg fielder.
On off, Foakes blocks it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Tossed up around off, Foakes plays for the incoming delivery but the ball straightens to go past the outside edge.
On  middle, defended.
On off, Broad lunges to play it to mid on.
On off, turn and bounce too. Broad looks to defend it but the ball takes the thigh pad and goes to the first slip.
Floated around off, dabbed to the off side with soft hands.
Drifting around off, pushed to the off side off the back foot.
Bowls a carrom ball around middle, Broad looks to defend it but at the last moment plays it to the leg side.
Going down leg, Broad looks to flick it but is beaten.
Short outside off, Foakes plays it to backward point.
Tossed up on off, Foakes blocks it.
Short on the pads, Foakes looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad away from the stumps.
Flighted on off, Foakes defends it off the outer half of his bat.
Tossed up on off, Foakes defends it.
Tossed up on off, Foakes blocks it.
Flighted on the stumps, Broad defends it.
On the stumps, SB keeps it out.
Short around off, Broad defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Stuart defends it.
Tossed up on off, Broad pushes it to cover.
Down the leg side, Broad looks to flick but misses.
Tossed up around off, Foakes looks to defend it but ends up getting a leading edge that runs to third man. A single taken.
Full on middle, turned towards mid-wicket.

OUT! CAUGHT! Axar gets his 5-fer and what a place to get his second 5-wicket haul. In his home ground, in the biggest cricketing ground in the world, and what a way to kick off the stadium's first cricket game. Broad decides enough of the defending lets go for some glory. That brings about his downfall. Floated delivery around off, Broad brings out the big sweep. He does not time it. He hits it high in the air but there is a man at deep square leg. He picks him up to perfection and Jasprit Bumrah theretakes a good catch.
On off, pushed away towards covers.
Floated on off, Foakes pushes it to mid off and gets to the other end.
Flighted around off, Anderson plays it to point.
FOUR! Introduction of seam brings runs. Full and on the pads, Foakes flicks it all along the carpet as the ball races to the fence at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length and on off, Foakes keeps it out to the off side. NO BALL! Bumrah has overstepped.
Short of good legnth and around off, Foakes plays it to the on side.
Shortish ball on middle, Foakes pulls to deep mid-wicket but does not take the run.
Pokes this one through cover-point and takes the single this time. 2 balls for Anderson to negotiate with.
Short of a length ball around off, Anderson sways away from it.
Yorker on middle, Anderson jams it out.
Floated on middle, Foakes looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat.
Tossed up on off, Foakes keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Foakes defends it.

OUT! BOWLED!  Axar gets the final wicket and what a superb performance this is from India and the local boy. Axar Patel finishes with a 6-fer. Tremendous from the left-arm spinner. Short and drifting in. Foakes gets on his back foot and looks to punch. He misses it completely but Axar does not. He hits the middle and off pole. ENGLAND BOWLED OUT FOR 112!
Edged but safe! Anderson starts with a good length ball pitching on off and shaping away. Rohit looks to defend but gets an outside edge. It goes to the left of gully but does not carry.
Another outswinger but this starts from outside off. Rohit leaves it alone.
Good ball! Carry and zip for Anderson. A little short outside off, it pitches and moves away a bit. Rohit looks to defend but gets beaten.
Length ball around off. Rohit looks to play but opts to leave. Too late as the ball hits his bat as he tries to take it up.
Good length ball outside off, Rohit shoulders arms to this.
Good length ball outside off, Rohit is happy to watch it carry to the keeper. Maiden to begin with.
Broad starts with a length ball around off, Gill taps it to point. He plays away from the body there. Could be risky with the ball moving.
Good ball! Length and outside off, Gill goes to have a feel for the ball as he pokes at it. Luckily for him the ball goes past the outside edge.
Length ball around off, Gill dabs it to point.

NOT OUT! Gill survives a nervy moment. Broad bowls a back of a length ball around off, Gill looks to block it off the back foot but ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to second slip where Stokes takes the catch and in confident that he has got his man. The third umpire is asked for as the replays roll in. The ball has clearly bounced before Stokes pouched it.
Length and around off, Gill leaves it alone.
On off, Gill blocks it from the crease.
Length and around off, Sharma defends it out off the back foot towards covers.
Another length ball in the channel around off, Rohit plays it but cannot get it past point.
On a length and around off, Rohit dabs it to covers for a single. Rohit off the mark here.
Length and around off, Gill plays it back to the bowler.
Length ball around off, Gill goes for the flick but is rapped high on the pads as the ball goes to point.
On a lenght and around off, Gill gets behind the line to block it out.
Length and around off, Sharma flicks it to the leg side this time.
Good length and in the channel outside off, Rohit is aware of his off pole as he makes a leave this time.
Full on off, driven straight to mid on.
FOUR! Gloriously driven! Full and around off, Rohit leans on and then drives it through mid off for a boundary. Hansome looking hit from the Hit-Man.
Good length and around off, Rohit stands tall to block it out.
Another length ball around ofl, Sharma defends it out.
Fuller on off, Gill blocks it to to the on-side.
Back of a length and around off, Gill dabs it to the off side.
Length and around off, Gill defends it in an  awkward manner towards the off side.
Length ball on off, Gill blocks it out off the front foot.
Length and outside off, Gill makes a leave.
Length ball on off, Gill keeps it out safely. THAT WILL BE DINNER ON DAY 1!
Length ball around middle, Sharma turns it to mid-wicket.
Good length and around off,  Sharma taps it off the back foot towards gully where Ollie Pope fields it.
FOUR! That should ease the nerves! Rohit continues from where he left. Full and around off, Rohit leans into the drive as he creams it through covers. The ball races to the fence in quick time.
Broad drags his length back a bit as he keeps it around off, Rohit hops to defend it to point.
Good ball! This is Broad's length. Length and in the channel around off. With a hint of inward movement. Rohit watches the ball and then leaves it alone.
Good length and around off once again, Rohit plays it from the crease this time.
Length and angled on middle, Gill somehow manages to fend it away to the leg side at the last instance.
Fuller and around off, Gill comes half forward to push it to mid on.
Anderson keeps it on a length and around off, Gill does well to defend it off the front foot and towards covers.
Short of good length on off,  Gill is rooted to his crease as he blocks it off the back foot this time.
Length and around off, Gill dabs it to gully.
On a length and around off, Gill punches it off the back foot towards point. Maiden for Anderson.
Good length and around off, Rohit dabs it to covers and takes a single on offer.
Short of good length and around off, Gill cuts but he chops it to cover-point.
Full and around middle, Gill turns it to mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Just clipping leg! Umpire's call it is! Length and angled into middle and leg, Gill looks to flick but misses to get rapped on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Root takes the review after consulting Broad. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge confirms that there is no bat involved as the Ball Tracker comes on. Umpire's call it is and Gill survives to fight it out.
Good length and around off, Gill watchfully plays it off the back foot.
On middle, Gill plays it to mid on to see off the over.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Another one wide outside off, Rohit once again lets it go behind.
This time Rohit pokes away from his body. Good length and just outside off, it shapes away. Rohit is on the back foot as he looks to punch it on the up. Misses as the ball moves away.
Gets behind the line this time and punches it towards the off side.
Shortish and just around off, poked towards the point region.
Driven nicely but for nothing! A maiden. Fuller and wider outside off, Rohit drives it towards the cover region.

FOUR! Crunched! Gill is finally off the mark but in style! Lovely stroke from him. A short ball, rare loose ball from Broad. Gill latches onto it and slams it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
What a comeback ball from Broad. This is good length and just outside off, it lands and takes off. Gill looks to force it on the off side but misses.
Around off on a length, solidly kept out.
Good length and around off, Gill defends it solidly.
Landed around off, just outside off. Gill comes on the front foot and blocks.
Solid behind the line again. A testing over.
Fuller length ball from Anderson and around off, Rohit taps it back to the bowler.
Anderson keeps it on a length and around off, Rohit closes the face of the bat to play it towards square leg for a single.
Gill has a good technique against pacers as he defends this length ball confidently towards covers off the front foot.
FOUR! Great shot! Short of good length and around off, Gill rocks on the back foot as he plays the short-arm jab through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length and around off, Gill chops it to covers this time.
Back of a length and around off, Gill hops and drops it towards covers to see off the over. Both the openers are watchful at the moment.
Fuller and outside off, no movement on this one as Rohit makes a leave.
Length and around off, it hurries onto Rohit. Sharma drops it with soft hands to the leg side.
Short and around middle, Sharma goes for the pull and hits it towards fine leg. Only a single results.
Length and around off, Gill punches it towards cover-point and takes a brace this time.
Fuller and targetting the base of off pole, Gill plays it to the bowler.
Length and outside off, Gill lets it be.
Length and around off from Archer, Rohit plays it from the crease.
Length and around off, Sharma defends it out once again.
FOUR! This man loves to pull and hook. Anything short and he will dispatch it. Short and around midlde, Rohit rolls his wrists and pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Sharma not only plays the pull but also the cover drive to perfection. This is a length delivery bowled around off, slight width offered and Sharma punches it off the back foot through covers as the ball races to the fence.
Back of a length ball, this one jags back in. Rohit works it through mid-wicket for one.
Bangs this one short but it is wide outside off. Left alone. 9 off Archer's first over.
Full and around middle, Sharma drives it to long on and takes a single.
Tossed up around off, Gill presses forward in defense this time.
Slightly flatter and around off, Gill taps it off the back foot.
Some turn and bounce for Leach! Tossed up ball outside off, Gill looks to poke at it but seeing the turn there decides not to play at it.
Floated around off, Gill defends it out safely.
Floated on middle, tucked through mid-wicket for one.
In the channel outside off, left alone by Gill.
Length ball angled in, Gill works it towards mid-wicket.

In the air... safe! That kicked off after pitching outside off. This one comes back in from around off, Gill looks to defend but gets squared up a bit. The ball takes the leading edge and goes towards point. It is uppish but short.
Good length and around off, Gill puhses it towards mid off.
Little too wide outside off. Gill lets it be.

OUT! TAKEN! Archer strikes and it is the short ball that does the trick for him. Gill wanted to take him on but the ball came quickly. That was short and wide outside off. Gill looks to drag it from there and deposit it out of the park via a pull stroke. He ends up getting it off the cue end of his bat. The miscued shot goes high in the air but as far as mid-wicket. Zak Crawley gets under it and takes the catch easily. A poor stroke from Gill. He did the hard work of getting his eyes in and then played a rash shot to get dismissed.
Short and wide outside off, Rohit punches it down to deep cover for one.
Pujara dances down first ball. Probably the way he is going to counter the spin. Leach tosses it up and just around off, Pujara comes down and drives it towards mid off.
Floated around off, Pujara this time blocks solidly.
Around off, kept out.

OUT! LBW! 4-ball duck for Pujara and Leach has done the trick for England. That looked plumb and hence Pujara didn't go for the review. This is a massive success for England. It is the arm ball from Leach which pitches around off and skids sharply. Pujara looks to defend off the front but misses to get hit on the pad. A big appeal follows and the umpire agrees with the bowler. Only inside edge can save Pujara. But he is having a word with his partner about the DRS. That means there is no inside edge. And he is walking off. Two wickets in the span of 6 balls. Ball Tracker rolled in a bit later and it showed that it would have crashed in the stumps. So, a good call from Rohit and Pujara to not review.
Floated around off, Virat lunges forward and keeps it out. End of a successful over from Leach.
Length and outside off, Sharma makes a leave.
Another pacy delivery from Archer but it is outside off, Rohit has no issue in leaving it.
FOUR! Rohit goes about his business! Short and on middle, Rohit swivels and then pulls it in front of square on the leg side for a boundary.
Short of good length and around off, Rohit dabs it to gully and looks for a single but it is not there.
Fuller and on off, Rohit dead bats it solidly.

FOUR! Top edge and it runs to the fence! Archer bangs it halfway into the pitch and gets it to hurry onto Rohit. Sharma goes for the pull but takes his eyes off it as the top edge flies over the keeper and to the fine leg fence for a boundary. Rohit is lucky as it could have lobbed straight up in the air.
Floated on off, Kohli defends it to the off side.
Bad ball from Leach! Full and dished down leg, Kohli looks to get bat on ball there but misses it. Ben Foakes to does not collect it. The ball runs to fine leg for a couple of byes.
Floated outside off, left alone.
On middle, Kohli leans a bit forward and then turns it to mid-wicket for a couple of runs now.
Slightly flatter and around off, Kohli dabs it to cover-point for a single.
Full on off, Rohit blocks it out.
Shortish and around off, Kohli hops and defends.
Length delivery, around off once again. VK is solid in defense.
Landed around off, kept out.
Just outside off, Kohli gets right behind to force it towards the gully region.
Back of a length and just outside off, poked towards the point region.
Back of a length and outside off, pushed towards the point region.

Quick single! Rohit's call and he was running to the danger end. Good running. Full and on middle, Rohit flicks it towards mid on. The fielder is on his toes and Rohit sneaks a single. Kohli was late in responding but he made it in.
Flat and turning away from around off, worked towards mid-wicket.
Trademark Kohli drive but there is a man in the deep. Overpitched and outside off, Kohli creams it through the covers and gets to the other end.
Now Rohit drives it nicely through extra cover for one. 50 up for the Indians.
Full and wide, forced to deep cover for a single.

NOT OUT! Going over the stumps. That didn't look that way but Ball Tracker says so. Rohit survives. Floated around off, Rohit takes a big stride forward, in fact he shimmies down a couple of steps and looks to defend but misses to get hit on the front pad. A huge, huge appeal follows but it is turned down. Leach and Root talk and then the England skipper reviews. Time for the replay. Clearly bat first. Ultra Edge confirms the same. Here's Ball Tracker. Missing. It is going over the stumps. England lose a review. That looked close but it is going over the timbers.

FOUR! BOOM! Welcome into the attack, Mr. Stokes! Stokes runs in and bangs the first ball short. Kohli says ok. Swivels on the front foot and plays a crunching stroke through mid-wicket. Crawley had no clue when it flew past him.
Full and angled on middle, Kohli strokes it to mid on and takes a single.
Length and angled on the hips, Rohit turns it to square leg for a single.
Short of good length and around off, Kohli blocks it right under his eyes.
Length and outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
Short of length and around off, Kohli hops and defends it to point.
FOUR! Rohit is just making it look so easy. Tossed up around middle, Rohit skips down the track a bit and then lofts it to long on for a boundary.
On middle. stroked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Oohs and aahhs! Slightly tossed up around off, Kohli looks to dab it to the off side but inside edges it past leg stump towards backward square leg. A couple taken.
Fuller and around off, Kohli drives it on the up but it falls short of the man at covers. A single taken.
Flighted outside off, Sharma makes a leave.
Fuller on middle, Sharma clips it through mid-wicket and gets a brace.
Fuller and around off, Kohli stays on the back foot as he blocks it out.
WIDE! Stokes bowls an effort ball but he ends up getting it rise up off the surface. Kohli leaves it. Wide called.
Short and around off, Kohli pulls it but cannot get it past the man at mid-wicket.
FOUR! This time Kohli succeeds to find the fence. Length and around leg, Kohli just works it through mid-wicket and it speeds to the fence in the deep. Quality from the Indian skipper.
Length and around off, Kohli clips it to mid-wicket.
Length and outside off, Kohli makes a leave.
Another one outside off, Virat shoulders arms to it.
Flatter and outside off, Rohit makes a leave.
Tossed up around off, Rohit taps it to point and takes a quick single.
Darted on off, Kohli comes on the front foot as he defends it out.
Fuller on off, driven towards backward point for run by Kohli.
On middle, Rohit paddles it behind square on the leg side. Leach appeals but nothing from the umpire. A single taken.
Flatter on off, Kohli plays it to point.
Short of good length and around off, Sharma plays the pull shot towards square leg. He takes a comfortable two.
Length and around off, Sharma defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length ball around off, Rohit pats it to cover-point.
FOUR! Rohit onto 49 now! Short of length ball around off, Rohit looks to force it off the back foot but ends up getting a thickish outside off. The ball flies towards third man for a boundary.

FIFTY FOR ROHIT! Another quality knock from the Hitman. It isn't easy out in the middle but it isn't impossible either. However, when Rohit gets going, everything looks easy. He is once again looking set for a big one. Just 63 balls for Rohit to get to his half ton. Stokes runs in and bowls a fuller ball on middle and leg. Rohit flicks it down to deep mid-wicket to get to the milestone.
Length and around off, Kohli pushes it off the back foot towards cover. A single is taken.
A fuller ball around off, pushed towards the off side.
Solid drive but for no run. A fuller ball outside off, VK comes on the front foot and strokes it towards the cover region once again.
Around off on a length, poked towards the gully region.
Just outside off on a good length. Left alone.
Good length and around off, Kohli is on the front foot.
Landed around off, kept out.
Floated around off, kept out.
Darted outside off, left alone.
Short and just outside off, punched towards the cover-point region for one. 50-run stand is up betwen the two.
Floated around off, Kohli is on the front foot to block.
Big turn! This one is tossed up and just around off, it lands and spins away sharply to beat the outside edge. Foakes cannot collect.
Little too full and it doesn't have the space to turn. Kohli pokes it towards backward point.
Back of a length and around middle, tucked to the man at mid-wicket.
Length and around off. Rohit blocks.
Good length and around off, comes in a tuck. It is tucked through square leg for one.
Shortish and around off, kept out.
FOUR! Poor, poor ball. Too short. Too wide. Kohli is not going to miss out. He punches it through the cover region and it races to the fence in the deep.
Just outside off on a length, poked towards point.
Floated just outside off, poked towards point.
Floated around off, Rohit is solid in defense.

Dropped? Yes! But that was just a stunning effort. Floated full and on middle, Sharma gets down and paddles it. Pope at short leg anticipates it early. He runs to his right and then realizes the ball is the other way. He sticks it left hand out and tries to catch. Gets a hand to it but fails to hold on. Will be called a dropped chance but that was quality work from Pope.
Flat and around middle, kept out.

A ripper! That lands just around off and rips past the outside edge. Foakes makes the keeping look so easy there. He collects to his right and breaks the stumps in a flash. Kohli wasn't going anywhere though so it won't matter. Quality ball to beat the outside edge and even better take from the keeper.
Darted short this time and VK strokes it to deep cover for one.

Droppped again! Pope again! This was a straightforward chance. Anderson cannot believe it. Big, big miss from Pope. Shortish and just outside off, Kohli stays back and looks chop it on the offf side. He tries to drag his bat away at the last moment. But Kohli is late and he ends up getting an outside edge. The ball goes to the right side of Pope who is manning the gully region. He gets both hands but spills the chance. How costly will this be?
Fuller and around off, kept out.
Gets behind the line again and is solid in defense.
Around off on a length, VK blocks.
Wide outside off, Kohli watches it go behind.
Shortish and around off, Kohli defends solidly.
Tossed up and outside off, Rohit pushes it towards the cover region

Ha, ha, ha. Funny scene! A tossed up ball, Rohit was going to play the paddle sweep. Stokes from first slip spotted that early and started running to his left, from behind the keeper. However, Rohit adjusts and blocks it on the off side. Stokes smiles as he returns to the first slip position.

NOT OUT! Rohit is in and he survives again. Tossed up and just around off, Rohit comes on the front foot and looks to defend but the ball rips past the outside edge and goes behind. Foakes shows his class and collects the ball and whips the bails off in a flash. He appeals. The square leg umpire takes it upstairs. Replays roll in. Rohit has his feet grounded.
On middle, kept out.
Play and a miss! Tossed up and outside off, Rohit looks to sweep but the ball lands and spins away. Foakes once again shows his skill and collects the ball nicely.
Darted outside off, Rohit lets it be.
Length ball around off, Kohli drives it straight to covers.
Extra bounce there! Length and around off, Kohli looks to defend it but the ball takes the shoulder of the bat and goes to mid-wicket. A couple taken.
Fuller on off, Kohli strokes it to covers for a single.
FOUR! Easily done! Poor fielding from Leach. Clearly tiring legs there. Full on midlde, clipped through mid-wicket as the ball races to the fence.
Length and around off, blocked off the front foot.
Back of a length and around off, Rohit is solid behind the line again.
Floated around off, kept out.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Leach gets the big wicket, just before the Stumps. Huge, huge wicket. Leach is pumped. Shake of the head from Kohli as he walks back with a dejected look on his face. This is floated nicely. It is around off, Kohli hangs on his back foot and looks to cut. That is too close for that shot but the Indian skipper does that. He ends up getting a bottom edge and the ball canons into the stumps. He did all the hard work, looked really good but has been dismissed just before the Stumps.
Floated full and around off, Rahane is solid in defense.
EDGY! Nervy few balls for the Indian vice-captain.

Edged again! Tossed up and just outside off, Rahane looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes uppishly towards Stokes at first slip. Ben dives to his right but misfields. A single taken.
Rohit keeps out the last ball solidly. This one is flat and just around off, Rohit stays back and bunts it on the off side. With this, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Anderson starts with a fuller ball on off, Rahane starts the day with a solid front foot defense.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it solidly off his back foot this time.
Fuller but not full enough on off. Rahane defends it onto the ground.
Good length ball on off, Rahane has no problems blocking it.
Much better from Anderson! Goes full outside off, a little bit of inswing late on. Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Maiden to begin the afternoon! Back of a length ball on off, Rahane defends it off his back foot and sees off the first over.
Flighted around off, turns away as Rohit comes ahead looking to block. Goes past the outside edge and to the keeper.
Flighted, around off, Sharma skips down the track and works this one to the mid off region for a sharp single. 100 up for India too.
Loopy on middle and leg, Rahane looks to block but it looks like he has missed it and the ball takes the pad and lobs towards the square leg region.
Good turn again by Jack! Goes fuller, around off, nice loop, turns away as Rahane misses his block.
Flatter this time, around off, moving away too as Rahane misses his pull this time.
Shows the full face of the bat to this full ball and smothers this one out.
Short of a length and around off this time from Jimmy, pushed away from the body to covers.
FOUR! First boundary of the afternoon and it comes off Rohit's bat. A gift to someone who has the batting caliber of RS! Short and wide outside off, slapped through point.
Around off, length, kept out by RS.

FOUR! Rohit makes look batting look easy and his stroke now has shown that again. A bright afternoon but his batting is lighting things up early on. Short of a length around off, Sharma goes on his back foot and punches this through covers. The ball speeds away to the ropes.
On a length and around off, Rohit Sharma pushes it back towards Jimmy.
Shows the full face of the blade to push the last ball, which is a good length one, to covers. 8 off this over.
Full, floated, on middle, Rahane comes ahead and blocks and the ball goes just next to the sticks as Rahane looks to push it away. It does not go onto hit the stumps though.
Pushed to the mid on region.
Full, tossed up, around off, Rahane goes on his knees and looks to sweep. Only manages to get an under edge as the ball goes on a bounce to Stokes, at first slip.
On off, pushed to covers. Rahane is still on 1, from 17 balls.
FOUR! SCORES ARE LEVEL NOW! Rahane gets the boundary, that he has been looking for. Jack goes fuller, on middle, nice loop, Rahane brings out the broom and sweeps this one to fine leg for a boundary.
A single to end the over and India ahead by a run too now. Flatter, around off, the vice-captain goes on the back foot and clips this through square leg.
Length on off, kept out.
Identical to the previous delivery, Ajinkya comes on the front foot and pushes this to short cover.
Good length, around off, pushed to short cover again. A loud and clear 'no' from Rahane, to Rohit, in regard to the single.

Short of a length ball around off, Rahane goes on the back foot and punches this one in the gap between the point and cover fielder. They take on and Rohit assumes there will be two as he was was halfway down the track. Realizes there isn't a double and scampers back. Holds his hands up to Rahane later and holds a wry smile on his face too.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Good length on off, blocked by Rohit Sharma.
Flighted on off, pushed away to the off side.

OUT! LBW! India lose a wicket very early on Day 2 and Jack Leach picks up his third wicket! Flatter, around off, comes on straight after hitting the deck, Rahane goes on his back foot, looking to slash this one but the ball gets his pad first and rolls to the off side. A loud appeal and the umpire agrees and raises his finger. Rahane comes ahead, and has a quick word with Rohit, from his crease. He does not think technology can help him and so he walks back. Jack continues to torment the Indians and this is what Root would have wanted starting Day 2!
Easy single to get off the mark. Full, loopy, on off, Pant plays this with soft hands through mid on for a single.
Flighted around off, RS prods forward. Blocks.
Similar sort of delivery as the last ball. Blocked out again by Rohit.
Now he comes down the track and pads the ball to the on side. A successful over for England and Leach.
PLAY AND A MISS! Length, around off, coming in with the angle as Rishabh looks to push this one away to the off side. Misses though and Ben Foakes collects.
In the channel of uncertainty outside off, this time, Pant is not tempted into the shot. Shouldered arms to.
Closer to the off pole and on off, making Pant get his bat across to keep this one out.
Presses forward to a full ball to block this to short cover.
Short of a length and outside off, Rishabh Pant slaps this one but can only find the point fielder.
Around off, length, Pant's block gets the ball to hit him on the pad, as the ball took the inner half of the blade. A maiden for Jimmy.

OUT! LBW! One brings two for Jack Leach and the dangerman for India, Rohit Sharma has to trudge back. Full, loopy too, just around the off pole, Rohit Sharma thinks about getting on his knees and sweeping this one away. He misses though and seems to have got hit just above the thigh pad. An appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Sharma walks across and has a quick word with Pant. Decides to take the review. Ultra Edge is not able to save him. Ball Tracker rolls in and the impact is deemed to be umpire's call. The wickets are hitting though and this will be out. India retain the review but have lose half their side, back into the hut now.

Shorter and outside off, slapped away through point by Ashwin. The fielder gives it a chase and seems to have pulled it back, just before the ropes. The umpires have a look and decide that this is a clean save. Two runs then for Ash to open his account.
Flighted outside off, spins away, left alone.
On off, played towards point.
Ravichandran Ashwin has just watchfully blocked this out.
Floated on off, pushed to covers now. Another great over for England. They remove the dangerous Rohit Sharma.

OUT! EDGED AND CAUGHT! The first ball that Joe Root bowls and he gets the big fish, Rishabh Pant. England have started off the day brilliantly as they have scalped 3 quick wickets. Root gives this one nice air and lands it around off, it lands and then turns away. Pant is tempted into having a feel of this one. All he manages to do is get a thin inside edge, which Ben Foakes gobbles up. A loud appeal and the umpire does not take long to raise his finger. Pant has a chat with Ashwin, but decides that the review will not do him any good. Walks back disappointed and England are on top at the moment.
Flighted around off, defended solidly off the front foot.
Loopy around off now, Sundar again blocks.
Flat, on off, Sundar goes on the back foot and keeps it out now.
Pushed to the cover region now.
Another over which will make the English players real happy. A wicket-maiden by skipper, Root. Flighted, around off, kept out solidly.

FOUR! The best form of defense? Is to attack! That's what Ashwin is probably thinking right now. Loopy, around off, Ashwin puts on his dancing shoes and lofts this one over mid on. Takes a couple of bounces and goes past the ropes.
Around off, full, blocked.
Presses forward to a fullish ball on off, to push it to covers.
Beautyyy! Peach from Leach now. Flighted around middle and leg, turns away from Ashwin as he comes ahead to block. Whizzes past the outside edge and into the keeper's mitts.
Defended to the square leg region now by Ash.
Tosses this one up and lands it on middle, Ashwin is solid in his defense.
Huge turn. Flighted around off, turns away as Sundar looks to defend.
The batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Flat, on off, kept out.
Fuller, outside off, flighted, Sundar drives this one to the cover fielder.
Around off, fuller, flighted, pushed to mid off.
Fuller, outside off, nice loop as well, Sundar shoulders arms to this one. Second maiden for Root.
Floated around off, Ashwin comes ahead to block. The ball takes the outer half of the blade and goes to gully.
Pushed to point this time.
Presses forward to block this one to covers now.
Shortish and outside off, slapped to covers again.
FOUR! Slashed and slashed away with power. Short, wide too, poor ball to someone who can bat as well as Ashwin does. Ravichandran slams this one through point.
On off, blocked out.

OUT! TIMBER! WOAHHH! Beauty of a delivery from Root and Sundar goes back for a 12-ball duck. Silence all around when the stump was hit. Root bowls this fuller and around middle, spins away sharply as Sundar comes ahead to block. He misses and the ball goes on to clip the top of the off stump. India lose another one and are staring down the barrel now!
Around off, full, pushed away to the off side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Axar Patel has tried to take the aerial route but loses the wicket in the process. Full, loopy, around off too, Patel thinks about starting his inning off with a boundary. Skips down the track and looks to slam this one over Sibley at short cover. Does not get the elevation and Dom Sibley takes this one nicely. Root has yet to concede a single run and he has already snared 3 quick wickets.
Full, flighted, on middle, tucked to the leg side by Ishant.
Around off, length, pushed away to the off side now.
Around off again, fuller, Ishant plays this one with soft hands towards point. What an over for England and Root! Third maiden for Root, in as many overs, and also 2 wickets off this over.
Floated around off, Ashwin defends it off his front foot.
Tossed up around off, Ashwin milks it away from short cover and towards long off for a single.
Oh ho! Short outside off, Ishant lunges forward and looks to defend but pulls his bat back inside the line.
Flighted outside off, Ishant looks to leave but he is a bit late as he chops it to slip.

This has went back to Chennai from Ahmedabad! That is how much this one has turned. Floated around leg, Ishant shoulders arms to it and the ball goes to Foakes at the fourth stump line. Foakes does well behind the stump to gather it.
Good leave! Tossed up around off and turning away. Ishant shows his skills with the willow as he leaves this one.
Darted full on middle, Ashwin pushes it to short cover.
Short on the pads, Ashwin dabs it to the right of short leg.
Tossed up on off, Ashwin blocks it.

FOUR! What a shot and that has seen the crowd found its voice back. First runs off Root's bowling and this is a fabulous hit. Floated on off and middle, Ashwin gets down on his knee and slaps his sweep through mid-wicket for a boundary. Takes the lead to 18.
On the pads, Ashwin keeps it out.
Nicely done! Ashwin farms the strike. Short and turning away from outside off. Ashwin runs it down away from the slip fielder and gets a single.
Tossed  up on off, Ashwin pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Ashwin milks it to long off but does not take the single.
Short on middle and leg, Ashwin comes down the track and dabs it onto the ground. The ball goes behind, to the left of Foakes.

Darted full outside leg. Ashwin looks to sweep but misses. The ball hits the pad and goes behind. There is a muted appeal but nothing from the umpire. The batters meanwhile run two leg byes. Lead over 20 now.

Floated on middle and leg. Ashwin gets on his front foot and looks to go inside out over covers. The ball though hits the inner half and goes behind square leg for one. One ball for Ishant to negotiate.
And he negotiates it! Flighted around off, Ishant looks to defend but gets an outside edge away from the man at gully.
Darted around the pads, Ashwin defends it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ashwin departs! Good catch from Zak Crawley and Root gets his 4th. 4/5 for the England skipper! WOW! Flighted outside off, Ashwin looks to take the attack to the England skipper. He looks to go for a big slog sweep. He has to fetch out for it and there is some extra bounce as well. It sees the ball hit the upper portion of the bat and go high in the air. Crawley at deep mid-wicket judges the catch well under the sun and takes a good catch. It has been a fruitful return for Crawley so far.
Floated on off, Ishant pushes it to cover.
Tossed up on the pad, Ishant flicks it to the on side.
On the pads, Ishant blocks it.

Ishant will now farm the strike! Floated around middle and leg, Ishant comes down the track and looks to hit it straight towards mid on. He gets a big inside edge and the ball goes towards mid-wicket. Single taken!

SIX! KABOOM! First six of the game and it is off the bat of Ishant Sharma out of all the people. He can surely wield a bat, there are no questions about it. Floated on off, Ishant goes over long off and marks his 100th Test with a biggie.
Flighted on off, Ishant blocks it.
Another couple and the lead has increased to 31 now. Valuable runs these. They are like golddust. Floated on middle and off, Ishant sweeps it away from deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Short around off, it keeps a bit low. Ishant manages to adjust, adapt and block it.
Big stride forward from Ishant. He negates the turn and blocks it.

Nicely bowled! Tossed up ball on off, Ishant looks to sweep but the ball turns and hits Ishant on the mid-riff region. He cannot keep the strike and Bumrah will face his first ball of the game in the next over.
Shouts for catch it but it fell away from Pope at short leg. Floated on middle, Bumrah takes a stride forward to defend but the ball hits his glove and falls away from Pope.
Floated on off, Bumrah defends it uppishly to the off side but there is no silly point.
Tossed up on middle, Bumrah hits it hard to mid on but can't get the single.
Darted fuller on middle, Bumrah dabs it onto the ground.
Around middle, Bumrah looks to defend but the ball goes behind square leg and they get a single. Another valuable run added to the total.
Loopy ball on middle, Ishant defends it and sees off the over. He is showing his faith in Bumrah here.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Excellent effort from Stokes but he cannot get to the rebound. Floated around off, Bumrah goes for a big slog sweep. It takes the outside edge and flies to first slip. Stokes jumps high, gets his hand on the ball. It pops up and behind. Stokes dives but cannot get there.
NOT OUT! Floated around off and turning away. Bumrah looks to defend but misses. Foakes whips the stump off. The umpire goes upstairs and replay finds Bumrah's feet to have gone nowhere.
Tossed up around off, Bumrah looks to sweep but misses.
Flighted on off, Bumrah defends it off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Excellent review from Bumrah. There is an inside edge before the pad and Bumrah survives. Floated on middle and off, Bumrah looks to defend but gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Bumrah instantly reviews it. Replay rolls in and it shows there is an inside edge and hence Bumrah did not hesitate even a little to take it upstairs.
Bumrah manages to see off Leach! Flighted outside off, Jasprit leaves it alone.

Confusion but safe in the end! Floated on the pads, Ishant slogs it behind square leg. Ishant wants two but Bumrah is not even looking. Ishant has to turn his bike around. Root cannot hold onto the ball and Ishant comes back in with a dive.

OUT! LBW! Root gets his first 5-fer in Test cricket. What a spell of bowling this has been from the England skipper. All the talk was about England playing a spinner short but the captain has delivered with the ball himself. Slightly shorter on middle and off, Bumrah looks to slog it across the line. He misses and gets hit on the back pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Bumrah takes it upstairs and it seems like it is just a hopeful review. Replay rolls in and Ball Tracker shows all red. Root finishes with 5/8. INDIA BOWLED OUT FOR 145! Lead by 33!

OUT! BOWLED! Wicket off the very first delivery! Crawley who was magnificent in the first innings has gone for a golden duck. The local boy stuck in his very first ball of the first innings and he has done the same in the second innings. Terrible start for England! Perfect one for India.  Axar starts with a slowish delivery pitching on off. He gives this one air, the ball drifts and does not turn. Crawley looks to defend expecting it to spin but gets beaten by the straighter one and the ball hits the middle stump. What a stunning game this is turning out to be.

NOT OUT! The review saves Bairstow! Terrible shot first up from Bairstow. He is on a pair and going for the sweep first up is a terrible choice. Bairstow has been given a lifeline here. Shorter delivery in middle, Bairstow looks to go for the premeditated sweep. He misses and gets hit on the mid-riff region. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Bairstow takes the review. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows the ball to be missing the stumps.

OUT! BOWLED! Bairstow does not last long. Axar does not get the hat-trick but gets a wicket off the third ball of the innings. What a peach of a delivery this is from Axar, the local boy. Once again horrible technique from Bairstow. Floated delivery pitching on middle. Bairstow gets on the front foot and looks to defend expecting it to turn. The ball does not. Jonny leaves a 'not-so-bravo' gap between the bat and pad. The ball goes right between those and hits the top of leg.
Shorter on off, Root gets on his back foot to defend but gets beaten due to the turn.
The skipper gets the tourists scoreboard going. Short around off and turning away. Root dabs it to backward point and gets a single.
Eventful first! Floated ball on off, Sibley blocks it and gets through the first over. A run and a two wickets off the first. Perfect for India.
Floated around off, Root drives it through covers and looks for two. The throw is at the bowler's end. Ashwin whips the bails off but Sibley is back in.
Darted around the pad, Root flicks it uppishly but away from short leg for one.
Shorter on off, Sibley defends it with a straight bat.
Flighted on off, Sibley flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Sibley gets off the pair and gets his first run of this Test! Floated on middle, Sibley flicks it through square leg and gets a single.
Dot to finish the over. England 2/5 after 2. They trail by 28 runs. Darted on middle and leg, Root manages to block it.
Flighted around off, pushed to the mid on region by Dom.
On middle, nudged to the right of the short leg fielder.
Around off, fuller, loopy, Dom skips down the track and clips this one through mid-wicket for one.
Around off again, shorter in length, Root goes on the back foot and looks to block. The ball takes the inner half of the blade and goes to the leg side.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.

Floated nicely, around off, turns away and misses Joe's forward defensive push. Pant collects and whips the bails, but Root was in the crease. A brilliant start for India and another good over by Patel!

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Pujara gets his fingertips to this one. Flighted, on leg, Sibley skips down and flicks this one uppish, to the left of Pujara, at leg slip, who gets his fingertips but is not able to hold on. Two runs.

NOT OUT! Ashwin was very confident but the wickets were missing this time around, due to the extra bounce. Flighted around middle this time, not much turn, as Sibley prods ahead, looking to block this one out. Misses and gets rapped on the pad. An appeal. A very, very, VERYYYYY excited appeal. But nothing from the umpire. Discussions going around and Ashwin wants the review. Kohli goes for it. Ultra Edge shows no bat. Ball Tracker shows that the on-field call was the right one as the ball seems to be missing the sticks.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Around off, flighted, Sibley's attempt to block only generates an outside edge, which goes to Rahane, at first slip, on the bounce.
Worked to the leg side for one.
Short, on the pads, clipped to square leg for one.
Flighted, around off, turns away sharply as Root looked to play at this, but seeing the turn, gets his bat closer to the body and lets it through to Pant.
Driven through covers for a single now by the English skipper.
On middle, fuller, kept out solidly by Dom.
Outside off, fuller, left alone now.
Around off, loopy, Dom skips down and pushes this one to mid on for a quick single.
Outside off, short, Joe pushes this one to point for one.
IN THE AIR...SAFE! Flighted on middle, Root comes down the track and flicks this one to the right of Gill, at short leg, to deep square leg, for a single.
On middle, clipped to the on side. Rotates the strike, does Sibley.
Tossed up and on middle, Joe Root gets on his knees, Sweeps it behind square on the leg side. One run.
On middle, turning away from Dom, to the leg side, left alone.
Tossed up on off, Dom comes ahead, looking to block but misses and gets hit on the pad. A stifled appeal but they know that the impact was outside off.
On middle, spinning down the leg side as DS leaves.
Prods forward to a full ball. Defended.
Flat, on off, Joe goes on the back foot and pushes this to point. Comes ahead but then goes back and denies the single.
Good, quick run. Flighted on middle, nudged to square leg for a quick single.
Pushed to covers now.
Outside off, fuller, driven but straight to the cover fielder.
On off, fuller, loopy, Dom Sibley prods forward to block.
Flighted, on middle, turns into Joe as he goes back and punches to the left of mid on for a couple of runs. England behind by 14 runs now.
On middle, tucked to the leg side.
Darted on middle again, spinning down leg as Root shoulders arms now.
Around off, shorter in length, Joe pushes this one away to the off side.
Flat, on off, Joe goes on the back foot and clips this one to short mid-wicket.
A chance to take the catch! Flighted on middle, Root just tucks this one in front of the short leg fielder but the ball falls short. Joe has a wry smile on this face.
Shortish, on off, nudged to square leg now.
Tossed up and around off, Dom comes ahead and blocks.

OUT! CAUGHT! The third wicket for Axar and England lose another one. Top decision from the on-field umpire! Axar gives this one air and lands it around off, Sibley gets on his knees and looks to slog sweep this one away to the leg side. Misses and the ball goes past him, into Pant's mitts. A loud appeal from the Indians and the umpire raises his finger. Hmm...Sibley takes the review straightaway, does not even consult Root, which would suggest that he knows he has not got any bat on this. Well, Sibley, looks like you were wrong as Ultra Edge shows a clear spike as the ball is going past the bat. The on-field decision stays and the local lad, Patel is on a roll. England are behind by 14 runs.
Stokes gets off the mark straightaway. Flatter, around middle, Stokes clips this one behind square on the leg side for a brace.
Short, around middle, defended to the on side.
Full, loopy, around off, whipped through mid-wicket for one. Another successful over from Axar. 3 runs but also a wicket off this one.
Full, floated, around off, pushed to the mid on region.
Short, on the pad, clipped through mid-wicket for a brace.
SWEEP AND A MISS. Flighted and around off, turns away and takes off after hitting the deck, Ben gets on his knees and looks to sweep this one away. Misses though.
Arm ball around off, Stokes blocks.
EDGY...SHORT! Tossed up and around off, Stokes looks to block but the ball takes the outside edge and goes and drops just in front of Virat, at second slip.

An appeal but turned down. Full, outside off, tossed up, Ben looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pad. Turned down by the umpire and there is some discussion, as to whether they need to take the review. Do not go for it in the end.
Clipped to the on side for a single.
Ben Stokes goes on the back foot and blocks.
Darted on middle, shorter in length, clipped to the mid-wicket fielder.
On middle again, kept out by Ben.
Full, on middle, shoots up after hitting the deck and hits him high on the pad.
Worked behind square on the leg side for one run. England still behind by 7 runs.
Full, almost yorker length, on middle, well dug out.
Big turn. Flighted around off, turns away with venom as Ben misses his defensive push.
On off, pushed to covers.
A full ball, loopy, Stokes presses forward and defends.
FOUR. Much needed boundary for England. They are now behind by 3 runs. Flighted, around off, Stokes gets low and sweeps this one through mid-wicket.

IN THE AIR...SAFE! Ben survives a scare. He was looking to take the charge but he does not lose the wicket on this occasion. Flighted, around off, Stokes goes for the sweep again but only manages to generate a top edge. Goes high up and lands in no man's land near mid-wicket. Two runs.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.
Pushed to the off side now by Joe.
Joe Root has just blocked that from his crease.
Flighted around off, Joe pushes this one towards covers for one.
On middle, swept away to square leg for one. England leading by one now!
Flighted outside off, Root looks to play at this one but the ball turns away and goes past the bat, to Rahane, at first slip.
FOUR! Incredible shot! Short and around leg, Stokes gets on his back foot and punches it off his back foot through mid-wicket. It has been hit with power and it goes to the fence.
FOUR! Reverse sweep now! Stokes has decided to take the attack now. Floated on middle and off, Stokes reverse sweeps it through point for a boundary.
Flighted outside off, Stokes looks to play but misses. The ball hits Pant's glove and goes to Kohli at second slip.
Tossed up on off, Stokes gets on his front foot and defends it onto the ground.
Flighted around off, Stokes looks to push it on the off side. The ball hits the outside edge and goes wide of second slip. Two taken. Takes the lead to 11!
Beauty to end the over. Flighted on off, Stokes looks to defend but the ball turns and beats the outside edge of Stokes' willow.
Around off, short, clipped through mid-wicket for a couple.
Shorter and on the middle and leg pole, Root goes back and looks to push this one away to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal but nothing from the umpire.
The batsman has just blocked that from his crease.

NOT OUT! Root survives! A very close call but the benefit of the doubt goes to Root! Patel bowls a full, tossed up ball just around off, Root comes ahead and looks to block this one out.
