Is not able to do so and gets smothered on the pads. A very loud appeal by the Indians and this time, the umpire raises his finger. Joe Root comes ahead and decides to have a chat with his partner, Stokes and in the end, makes the 'T' symbol. The ball is in between the bat and the pad and so, the third umpire has a couple of looks at this one, from different angles too. It seems to be real close and in the end, the third umpire decides to go the way of the batter and has the on-field umpire reverse the decision.
Outside off, loopy, spins away and Joe misses his push away.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Good ball! Short and turning away with some extra bounce. Stokes looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on his back leg's thigh pad.
Flighted fuller outside off, Stokes pushes it to point for a single.
Floated on off, Root pushes it back to the bowler.
Darted quicker on middle and leg, Root blocks it.
Sharp spin and bounce. Root looks to defend it outside the line of off pole but misses and gets hit high on the pad.
Reverse sweep now. Floated on middle and off, Joe reverse sweeps it behind point and keeps the strike.
Short, wide, outside off, slapped away through point for one.
Tossed up and around off, Stokes gets low and looks to sweep this one but misses and gets rapped on the pad. The impact was outside off and hence, there is not much of an appeal.
On off, played towards point.
Tossed up and on middle, Ben sweeps this one to fine leg. One run.
An inside edge this time. Floated and around off, Root prods ahead and looks to block this one out but inside edges it, onto his pad. An appeal but the umpire shakes his head.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Darted on leg, Ben looks to block but misses and get hit on the pad.

OUT! LBW! Ashwin gets his bunny again and this is the 11th time that Ashwin has got Stokes in Tests! The fourth wicket falls now and Stokes' poor run in this series will continue. Ashwin bowls a full ball, gives it nice loop and lands it around off and middle, Stokes comes ahead and looks to block this one out but misses. Gets rapped on the pad and the Indians go up, in appeal. The umpire does not take long to raise his finger. Stokes walks across to his skipper, Root and has a chat but Ben has a look, of someone who is not too confident. He looks to walk back, but Joe stops him and it looks like they will go for it, with around 2 seconds left on the timer. But, in the end, Ben probably says no and decides to walk off. India doing well to chip at these wickets. England leading by 17 runs.
Floated around off, Pope looks to push it away but fails to get any bat on this.
Outside off, left alone by Pope.
Flighted on middle, Ollie comes down the track and pushes this to the on side.
FOUR. Ollie Pope gets off the mark with a reverse sweep. This is on middle, full, flighted, Pope gets low and reverse sweeps this one to the third man fence.
Floated on middle, Root defends it with a straight bat.
Tossed up on off, Root sweeps it towards square leg and gets a single.
Another beauty! Pope is dancing against the turning ball so far! Floated around off, Pope looks to defend but misses and it goes past the outside edge.
Flatter on middle, Pope punches it to mid on and takes a quick run.

OUT! LBW! The big wicket, the big fish, the England captain Joe Root, who was looking good out in the middle is out of here and England have half their side back in the hut with the lead just at 23. Axar gets his 10th of the game and playing just his second Test, he now has a 10-wicket game as well. What a bowler! No Jadeja, no problem. The local by has done the job for his nation here at his home venue. Tremendous feeling for Axar. He would have dreamt of this moment as a child and he has achieved his dreams. The round arm action of Axar once again does the trick. Floated on middle, the ball skids off the surface and comes straight. Root looks to defend but gets beaten and the ball hits him on the pad. A huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Root does not even bother reviewing this as he knew that this one was plumb.
Floated outside off, Foakes leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Pope punches it to cover and gets a couple,
Tossed up around leg, Pope comes out in desperation and looks to whack one over on the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pad.
Flighted around off, Pope turns it to square leg and gets to the other end.
Flighted around off, Foakes defends it off the front foot.
A nicely looped up delivery on middle. Foakes flicks it to the leg side and gets his first run of the game.

EDGED BUT AWAY! Floated on middle and leg, Pope looks to defend but gets an inside edge courtesy an inside edge. The ball lobs off his pad and luckily for Ollie it falls away from Shubman Gill at short leg.
Flighted from wide off the crease. Foakes lunges forward and blocks it.
Tossed up around off, Foakes gets on his front foot to defend but the ball turns and beats his outside edge.
Darted on leg and skidding away. Foakes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Quick single! Floated on off, Foakes pushes it to the right of Washington Sundar at mid off and takes a quick run.
Flighted on off, Pope blocks it.
A very loopy ball around off. Pope pushes it to mid off. When he does that, there is a host of dust that puffs out of the surface.
Floated on off, Foakes defends it to the leg side with the spin.
Tossed up on off, Foakes defends it to mid on.
Flighted on middle, Foakes pushes it to the left of mid on and takes a run.
Floated on off, Pope defends it.

FOUR! That has beaten everyone! Oh there is some glove! Ashwin bowls this slower and gives this air around off. Pope looks to sweep but misses it. Pant misses it as well and the ball goes to the fence. Ashwin is surprised that it has been given as a boundary.

OUT! BOWLED! Ashwin gets the better of Pope. AGAIN!  Another one bites the dust and England are into the bowlers now. Floated delivery pitching on middle, Pope looks to defend but the ball pitches, turns and bounces away from him. The Englishman is completely squared up as the ball goes past the outside edge to hit the off pole. 6 down for 66 but effectively the tourists are 33/6!
EDGED BUT FALLS SHORT! Short around off, Foakes looks to defend but the ball turns and hits the outside edge. Foakes does well to dab it away from the man at second slip.
On the stumps, Foakes keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted on off, Foakes looks to defend but the ball grips away and beats the outside edge of Ben's willow. Pant too cannot hold onto it.
Quicker ball on the pads, Foakes looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Flighted on off, Foakes drives it through covers and gets a couple.
Around off, full, kept out.

OUT! LBW! As plumb as it gets! Ashwin gets his 400th Test wicket and India or shall we say the Indian spinners have spun a web around the England batters, which they have not been able to get past. Darted fuller on middle, Archer looks to whack it across the line. He misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises the finger. Archer decides to send it upstairs. No saving the big man as Ultra Edge first shows no bat and then Ball Tracker shows all red. Victim number 400 for Ashwin and he becomes the second fastest to the feat. He is happy and so are his teammates. He shows the ball to the crowd and he might keep this pink ball.
Floated on middle, Leach defends it.
Tossed up on off, Leach blocks it.
Floated on off, Leach manages to keep it out.
Play and a miss! Floated around off, Leach looks to play but misses.
Floated on off, Ben manages to squirt it behind point for a run.
Darted on middle and leg, Leach looks to defend but misses. Going down leg hence the muted appeal is turned down.
Flighted around leg, Leach comes down the track and looks to whack it on the leg side. He misses and gets hit on the pad.
Flighted on off, Leach defends it off the back foot.
SIX! Where has that come from! Leach has put on his dancing shoes and got off the mark with a biggie! Floated on off, Leach comes down the track and whacks it with the spin over long on for a biggie.
Shorter on off, Leach defends it off the back foot to see off the over.
Floated outside off, Foakes looks to whip it to the leg side but misses and gets hit on the pad outside the line of off stump.
Tossed up on off, Foakes defends it.
Good take! Short and spinning away, Foakes looks to flick but misses as the ball tums a mile. Pant does well to take the ball behind the stump.
On the pads, Foakes flicks it to mid-wicket.
On the pads and short. Foakes flicks it behind square on the leg side. He looks for a run but does not get it.
Darted on the pads, Foakes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad away from the stump.
Flighted on middle and off, Leach defends it.
Whacked over to the leg side but there is Rohit Sharma guarding the boundary on the leg side. Just a run.
Short and on off and middle. Foakes manages to get his bat down in time as the ball kept low.
Floated on off, Foakes flicks it towards mid-wicket and gets a run.
Floated on middle and leg, Leach defends it to the on side.
Was that a catch? Short and turning back in. Leach looks to defend but the ball cuts him in half. It goes very close to the glove. Pant, behind the stumps, cannot hold onto it either.
Full, flighted, on middle, Ben keeps it out.
Ben Foakes uses his feet well and flicks this one through mid-wicket, to wide long on for a single.
On middle and leg, Jack looks to defend this one out but misses and get hit on the pad.
Short, outside off, Jack looks to go back and defend but the ball takes the thigh pad and goes to the silly point fielder.
That is defended solidly off the front foot.
Punched to the long off region by Jack for a single. England leading by 46 runs now.
In the air but well short! Short around the pads, Leach whips it uppishly but away from square leg for a single.

OUT! LBW! Axar gets his 5th of the innings. Becomes the first bowler in Tests to pick up 11 wickets in a Day-Night Test.  Ben Foakes' battle out in the middle comes to an end and England lose yet another review. Another ball that does not turn off the surface has got the wicket. Round arm delivery pitching on middle, Foakes looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Foakes reviews it. Ultra Edge rolls on and after a lot of replays, it is confirmed that the ball did not hit the bat. Time for the Ball Tracker and it shows all red.
Flighted on off, Broad defends it.
Flighted on off, Broad blocks it.
Nicely tossed up on off, Broad keeps it out.
No run. Huge turn and a good take from Pant! Floated on middle, Broad looks to play the sweep but misses as the ball turns from east to west. Pant does well behind the stump not to concede the byes.
Floated outside off, turns away as Leach makes a calculated leave.
Floated around off, turns away again and misses Jack's forward defensive push.
On off and middle, Jack manages to chop this one, back onto his pad.

OUT! CAUGHT! Leach looked to drive and Ashwin picks up another! The end is nearing for England now. Ashwin bowls a full ball, outside off, gives it nice air, enticing Leach to go for the big booming drive through the off side. All Jack manages to do is induce an outside edge, which goes to Rahane, at first slip, who takes it nicely. India one wicket away from dismissing the visitors and England lead by 47 runs.

Brilliant take from Rahane but it has not kissed anything and beaten everything. Floated on middle, Anderson looks to defend but misses. The ball hits Pant's glove. Rahane dives to his right and takes it on the full.
Flighted on off, Anderson plays it well to defend it.
Floated outside off, Broad looks to defend but misses.
Flighted outside off, Broad leaves it alone.
Short and spinning away. Broad plays it with the spin towards backward point for one.

OUT! CAUGHT! That is the end of England's innings! Anderson has been given caught behind and they are out of reviews so Anderson cannot do anything. Floated outside off, Anderson looks to play the reverse sweep but gets a feather on it. Washington Sundar takes a very good catch and Sundar ends the game with a wicket in the solitary over he bowls. ENGLAND BOWLED OUT FOR 81! INDIA NEED 49 TO WIN!
Floated delivery around off, it spins away from Rohit. Sharma leaves it.
Tossed up delivery around off, Sharma once again it happy to let that go.
Tossed up on off and turning away. Rohit looks to get bat on ball for the first time in this innings and he misses it.
Misfield and India will get off the mark! Floated on off, Rohit drives it to point. Anderson lets the ball go through him and he gets a couple to get off the mark.
Short on the pads, Rohit gets on his back foot and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pad.

Excellent from Archer! A rare full toss on middle, Rohit whips it through mid-wicket. Archer gives it a chase and it looks like the ball will easily beat him to the fence. Archer though sprints and then puts the dive to save a run for his side.
Root starts with a short around off and middle. Rohit tucks it behind square leg for a single.
Flighted on leg, Gill comes down the track and pads it away.
Gill is off the mark! Short on off and middle. Gill tucks it to mid-wicket for a run.
Short around off, Rohit taps it to point.
FOUR BYES! Flighted down the leg side, Rohit looks to flick but misses. Foakes misses it as well and the ball goes to the fence.
Shorter on the pads, Sharma defends it to see off the session. DINNER ON DAY 2!
FOUR! A great stroke to get the last session underway. First boundary in this inning for young Gill. Flat, around off, Gill swivels and pulls this one nicely through mid-wicket.
Floated around off, pushed to the fielder at covers.
Gives it nice flight, outside off, spinning away and Gill makes a calculated leave.
EDGY! Flighted around off, turns away as Gill looks to block it out. Takes the outside edge, goes past Ben at first slip, towards third man for a brace.
Short, wide, slashed away to the point fielder.
Darted on the middle pole, kept out by Shubman. 6 runs off this over. India need just 32 more runs now!
Short and on middle, kept out by Rohit.
Shortish on middle again, Rohit goes back and fends this one to the on side.
Tossed up and on leg, Rohit pads this one away to the leg side.
Leg bye. Tossed up again, on leg too, Rohit looks to tuck it away but misses and the ball takes the pad and goes to the right of short fine leg. The batters take a leg bye.

FOUR BYES. Just not England's game. Nothing going their way now. You can't blame Foakes for this one. Flighted, but down the leg side, spinning away as well and Foakes is not able to grab this one. The ball races away to the fine leg fence.

SIX! Plays this shot so well. Gill wants to hurry back, by the looks of things. Full, tossed up, around off, Gill puts on his dancing shoes and skips down the track. Slams this one over long on for a biggie. 21 more needed.
Short, around off, punched to covers.
Flighted on middle, Rohit presses forward and defends it out.
FOUR! This time Rohit goes for the boundary. Uses his feet well too. Loopy and around off, Sharma dances down and powers this through mid on for a boundary.
Well fielded by Jimmy this time. Shortish and outside off, Rohit goes back and slaps this one through point. Anderson does well to shuffle to his right and stop the ball.
Flat, on off, pushed away to point.
Full, loopy, on middle and leg, Sharma prods ahead and looks to block but seems to have missed it. Gets hit on the pad and the English players register a tame appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Short, on off, kept out.
Flat again, outside off, slapped away but straight o Archer at point.

NOT OUT! The review was more in hope, than anything else from Root. Full, flighted, on middle and leg, Gill comes down the track and looks to pad this one away and does so. The players appeal but the umpire does not think so. Root goes for the review as he tries his luck. No shot offered and hence, no Ultra Edge is needed. Ball Tracker shows that the wickets would be missing. Not out, it will be.
Comes down the track and clips this one through mid on for a single by Gill.
Full, yorker length, on middle and leg, dug out by Rohit to the on side for a single.
Loopy on middle, whipped through square leg for one. Gill retains the strike for the next over. 14 more needed for the Indians.
On off, blocked.
Short, around off, keeps slightly low too and pushes it to point.
Around off, flatter, pushed to point again.
Presses forward to this full ball. Defends it out solidly, does Shubman Gill!
Shortish and on middle, nudged to the leg side now.
Full, tossed up, on middle, punched to the cover region.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Crawley is the culprit this time. Full, flighted, around off, Sharma gets on his knees and slogs this one towards the deep mid-wicket region. Zak runs to his left, tumbles and lets the ball through. 10 runs needed now.
FOUR! This was slammed away by Rohit! Root drags his length back and bowls a short one outside off, Sharma hammers this one through the covers for a boundary. 6 more needed now!
Full, yorker length, on middle, Rohit digs this one out. The crowds want Rohit Sharma to finish things off with a biggie!

SIX! THAT'S THAT! Rohit Sharma listens to the crowd and finishes the game off with a maximum! Root goes fuller, flighted, around middle and off, Sharma skips down the track and bangs this one over deep mid-wicket. INDIA WIN BY 10 WICKETS AND ALSO LEAD 2-1 IN THE SERIES!
